  "markdown": "# Lecture 8 - Localization: Particle Filter¶\n\n**Overview:**\n    \n\nIn this lecture we will understand particle filters in general, and especially particle filters used for Monte Carlo localization so for localizing robot in an environment given that we have a map.\n\n**Topics Covered:**\n    \n\n  * Map making with Hector SLAM\n\n  * Particle Filter Localization\n\n  * Adaptive Monte Carlo Localization (AMCL)\n\n  * Recursive Bayes Filtering used in AMCL\n\n  * Tuning Particle Filters in ROS First race of the semester!! See [Race 1](../../assignments/races/race1.html#doc-race1) for more information on how to setup and evaluate the race.\n\n\n\n\n**Slides:**\n\n> **Video:**\n\n> **Links to additional resources:**\n    \n\n  * [RoboRacer Simulator Repo](https://github.com/f1tenth/f110_ros/tree/master/f110_simulator)",
